When you are in the health, wellness, and weight loss space, January is an absolute whirlwind…

It’s the month that I personally struggle to take care of my own health because my companies are so focused on helping others.

I was working out this afternoon and ran into a friend I haven’t seen in months.

His first words were “you look shredded and your hair looks amazing!” 

I started laughing because I thought he was giving me a hard time, because I have been giving myself a hard time.

He was serious and was like “look at your reflection in the glass bro!”

It was a weird moment. Our perspective can literally change how we see things. 

That compliment was a blessing and a bit of a wake up call.

Working nonstop

Fasting literally 21 hours a day

And all the other things life throws at us can get us feeling down on ourselves.

Thank you God for that voice today.
Thank you God for my health, I am blessed.
Thank you God for all the opportunity.
Thank you God for the strength and wisdom to do it!

PS - who needs to get in the best health of their life? 

Holla!
#newyearsresolution #wellness #fitness #fitover40 #selflove #selflove #blessed #january #hormonehealth #peptidetherapy #sunsoutgunsout

In order to change your life, you first must change the way you think.

What limits have you set on your beliefs?

What unreal rules have you decide are real?

Are you focused on intention, action, and outcome? Are all 3 aligned? 

Do you even ask yourself these hard questions?

I started doing these 10 years ago when I was around 33 years old.

I decided I wanted to metaphorically beat the garbage out of my mind, my beliefs, my habits, and refill only with things that aligned with the future I wanted to create for myself.

This is the hardest and most rewarding thing you can do for yourself, your family, and your legacy. 

I started this process with a decision to change who I was instead of the lie society tells you which is accept who you are. 

No excuses, no looking back, no fear, just forward.

I decided to start reading books of others that did the same thing. Here are a few!

Luke 23:39 - 43 is one of my favorite verses in the Bible. We are all criminals of some level of imperfection compared to God.

Just like the two being crucified next to Jesus, but there is a difference. One criminal doesn’t believe and mocked Jesus requesting He prove who He claims to be by saving Himself, but the criminal didn’t understand God’s plan. We as humans are so short sited when it comes to God. We are infants to His understanding, and our ego will always get in the way, unless we work to remove ego.

The other criminal believes and he asks for forgiveness, Jesus acknowledges him and also promises he will be with Jesus in Heaven. 

It doesn’t get anymore beautiful than that!

What criminal will you choose to be?

39 One of the criminals hanging beside him scoffed, “So you’re the Messiah, are you? Prove it by saving yourself—and us, too, while you’re at it!”

40 But the other criminal protested, “Don’t you fear God even when you have been sentenced to die? 41 We deserve to die for our crimes, but this man hasn’t done anything wrong.” 42 Then he said, “Jesus, remember me when you come into your Kingdom.”

43 And Jesus replied, “I assure you, today you will be with me in paradise.”

I love history, especially my family history!

I was blessed with the opportunity today to visit my family cemetery outside of Waco, Texas.

The Lamb Family originally came over from England in the 1600s.

From British Colonial Va to North Carolina, to Alabama and finally to Texas. 
They fought in the revolutionary war, civil war, and many other battles along the way.

It’s amazing that over 150 years since my ancestors arrived in Texas, my family moved here. 

I think of the luxuries we have today in society and how incredibly hard life must have been for the brave  Americans that battled their way west. It’s humbling.🥺🇺🇸

I’m grateful for our progress. In all areas. 🙏🏼

Happ 4th, America! 
Greatest place ever. 
🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸

How many of you know the story of the city of Jericho in the Bible?
🤷🏼‍♂️
For reference it’s in Joshua 6 and 7. I suggest you read through to Achan’s sin. Achan’s name in Hebrew means “He that troubleth.”
🤯
What you tolerate, you accept. All through out our lives, in our families, in our communities, businesses, etc we can make the mistake of allowing what we know to wrong and that will bring problems, not prosperity. 
😢
If I were to look at society today I think we would all agree that we have problems and corruption, but how do we solve it? We can’t stone them like the Israelites did to Achan. Jesus has told us to love, especially our enemies.
🤦🏼‍♂️
It’s hard, but we can tell them the truth, point out their wickedness, praying for them to get saved, because that is actually what we Christians are called to do.
🙏🏼
Again, to be clear. We are not to tolerate wickedness or condone it. Being quiet is quietly promoting. Being tolerant is silently saying you are okay with it. 

Ephesians 5:11 “  Take no part in the unfruitful works of darkness, but instead expose them.“
❤️
James 4:17 “So whoever knows the right thing to do and fails to do it, for him it is sin.”
❤️
Galatians 6:1 “ Brothers, if anyone is caught in any transgression, you who are spiritual should restore him in a spirit of gentleness. Keep watch on yourself, lest you too be tempted.“
❤️
1 Timothy 5:20 “As for those who persist in sin, rebuke them in the presence of all, so that the rest may stand in fear.”
❤️
❤️
❤️ we are called to save them!
James 5:20 “Let him know that whoever brings back a sinner from his wandering will save his soul from death and will cover a multitude of sins.”
🙏🏼
John 3:16 ““For God so loved the world, that he gave his only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish but have eternal life.”
🙏🏼

Often times as Christians we are taught to believe that God doesn’t want to bless us here on Earth and our only blessing is in Heaven. 
🤷🏼‍♂️
That is false. All throughout the Bible God blesses His obedient people.  He blesses those that have true faith and belief in Him and the Word.
❤️
Does that mean money? No, not necessarily. It can be opportunity, it can be wisdom, it can be peace, it can joy, etc.
🙏🏼
Most of the time our limited thinking, lack of faith, and inconsistent obedience can lead to us not seeing the blessing. Here are a few scriptures:
“Ask, and it will be given to you; seek, and you will find; knock, and it will be opened to you.” (Matthew 7:7)
- do you even ask God or are you leaning on yourself?
“I have come that they may have life, and that they may have it more abundantly. (John 10:10)
- Jesus didn’t come so you can “just make it.”
“And God will generously provide all you need. Then you will always have everything you need and plenty left over to share with others. (Corinthians 9:8)
- are you selfish? Do you share? Do you bless others? 
😍
There are many story’s, promises, and proof today of the blessings of God in all forms. If you believe the Bible, you should also believe there is no limit to what He can do, you just have to get in the flow of the Holy Spirit and have faith.
🧑🏼‍🌾
Are you sowing into the Kingdom? There is no harvest without seed. What are you planting? 
Victory or defeat?
Love or hate?
Selflessness or selfishness?
Using money or hoarding money?
Righteousness or sin? 
🤷🏼‍♂️
It’s all a choice. Get around some Holy Spirit filled believers that can help you grow in your faith! I pray prosperity over you in Jesus Might name! 🙏🏼

The 2 biggest problems I see with entrepreneurs I coach:
🤯
1. They do t want to do the work. They want to be the boss, delegate most tasks because they want their free time or they “aren’t good at that”.

2. Entrepreneurs that just become there own over worked under paid employee. “No one can do it as good as me” mentality. They want to do it all, never willing to hand over tasks and areas of the business to others. I have been guilty of both of these my self and still am in some form.
🤯

The proper goal should be to create the process, document the process, train others on the process, have them reach you back the process, then have them teach others on the process. That is the formula to scale.
😎
If you begin this stuff day 1, it is way easier to scale the business. If not, it can be so hard.
🥵
I pray that this message blesses you today and in your future!

I have helped many sales people and other organizations revisit their sales process based on this method.
🚀
Mindset Conversion. 
🤯
We should not be selling, we should be exploring the options for an ideal outcome for a customer.
☝🏻☝🏻☝🏻
It begins with questions like this:
1. Where are you at now?
2. How do you feel about where you are now?
3. How did you get where you are? 
4. Is where you are working for you?
5. Why is it working or not working?
6. What do you want?
7. Why do you want it?
8. How would you feel if you got what you wanted?
9. What is in the way of getting what you want?
10. What would be required for you to over come that obstacle?
🤷🏼‍♂️
Ask yourself these questions… 
#sales #mindset #coach #winning #motivation #success
